Description: Three joining fragments of wall of perhaps Attic black-glazed pottery dinos or possibly krater; wholly glazed but misfired over most of exterior.
Curator's comments: Found unregistered. Almost certainly from the same dinos as 1886,0401.678-680 and 1965,0930.512. The streaky glaze under the rim differs among these pieces, but also on individual sherds, indicating that it varied around the pot.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.2203)
